Project overview (May 20, 2026)

Summary
- Repository hosts a Next.js 16 app under frontend/ for the Shared Service Facilities UI.
- backend/ exists but is empty (no server code yet).
- Root has a README.md from create-next-app and a package-lock.json without a root package.json.

Structure
- frontend/ contains the Next.js app, Tailwind v4, ESLint, and TypeScript config.
- frontend/src/app uses the App Router with route folders and shared UI components.
- frontend/public includes branding and decorative assets (SSF/DTI logos, background, hexagons).

Frontend (Next.js)
- Framework: Next.js 16.2.4, React 19.2.4, TypeScript 5.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 (via @tailwindcss/postcss) plus globals in frontend/src/app/globals.css.
- Fonts: Geist, Geist Mono, Inter, and IM Fell Great Primer set in layout.tsx.
- Dependency note: @supabase/supabase-js is installed but not yet used in the UI files scanned.

Routes (App Router)
- / (frontend/src/app/page.tsx): simple landing shell rendering NavigationBar with a mock user.
- /login-page: full-screen branded login view with mock auth, toasts, and form components.
- /province-page: province dashboard with search, grid of ProvinceCard tiles, and mock data.
- /project-page: projects list/cards grouped by year with filters, pagination, modal form, and mock CRUD.
- /file-page: project file list with search, upload modal, delete action, and mock file data.
- /account-page: account management table with filters, pagination, create/edit modal, and mock CRUD.

Key components (frontend/src/app/components)
- Navigation and layout: navigation-bar, footer, profile-badge.
- Inputs and forms: input-field, upload-field, forms-container, dropdown, search-bar.
- Feedback and actions: dynamic-buttons, dynamic-toast, status-badge.
- Data display: project-card, project-card-details, province-card, pagination, table-header/body.
- Icons: icons.tsx provides shared SVG icon components.

Mock data and behavior
- Most pages use in-memory arrays and simulated async functions (setTimeout) for create/update/delete.
- Validation logic exists on account and project forms; errors are surfaced via toast notifications.

Config and scripts
- Scripts (frontend/package.json): dev, build, start, lint.
- Next config uses the default empty NextConfig object (frontend/next.config.ts).

Notes
- Root-level npm install fails because package.json is inside frontend/.
- backend/ is a placeholder for future server/API work.
